    {
      "upanishad": "prashna",
      "verse_number": 14,
      "tags": [
        "Brahman",
        "sixteen parts",
        "Purusha",
        "rivers",
        "ocean"
      ],
      "sanskrit": "अरा इव रथनाभौ प्राणे सर्वं प्रतिष्ठितम् | ऋचो यजूंषि सामानि यज्ञः क्षत्रं ब्रह्म च ||२.६||",
      "transliteration": "arā iva rathanābhau prāṇe sarvaṃ pratiṣṭhitam | ṛco yajūṃṣi sāmāni yajñaḥ kṣatraṃ brahma ca ||2.6||",
      "word_meanings": [
        {
          "word": "अराः रथनाभौ",
          "meaning": "spokes in a wheel hub"
        },
        {
          "word": "प्राणे सर्वम् प्रतिष्ठितम्",
          "meaning": "everything is established in prana"
        },
        {
          "word": "ऋचः यजूंषि सामानि",
          "meaning": "Rig, Yajur, Sama Vedas"
        },
        {
          "word": "यज्ञः क्षत्रम् ब्रह्म",
          "meaning": "sacrifice, power, and Brahman"
        }
      ],
      "english_translation": "As spokes are established in a wheel hub, so everything is established in prana — the Rig, Yajur, Sama Vedas, sacrifice, power, and Brahman.",
      "shankara_bhashya_sanskrit": "अराः रथनाभौ — नाभौ अराः प्रतिष्ठिताः। तथा प्राणे — सर्वम् — वेदाः यज्ञाः — प्रतिष्ठितम्।",
      "shankara_bhashya_english": "Shankara: Just as all spokes of a wheel are established in the hub, so all the Vedas, sacrifices, and all of existence are established in prana (Brahman). Prana is the hub of the wheel of existence."
    },
    {
      "upanishad": "prashna",
      "verse_number": 15,
      "tags": [
        "Brahman",
        "knower",
        "liberation",
        "Pippalada",
        "final"
      ],
      "sanskrit": "एतावदेवाहमेतत्परं ब्रह्म वेद | नातः परमस्तीति ||६.७||",
      "transliteration": "etāvad evāham etat paraṃ brahma veda | nātaḥ param astīti ||6.7||",
      "word_meanings": [
        {
          "word": "एतावत् एव",
          "meaning": "only this much"
        },
        {
          "word": "एतत् परम् ब्रह्म वेद",
          "meaning": "I know this supreme Brahman"
        },
        {
          "word": "नातः परम् अस्ति",
          "meaning": "there is nothing beyond this"
        }
      ],
      "english_translation": "'Only this much do I know of this supreme Brahman. There is nothing beyond this.'",
      "shankara_bhashya_sanskrit": "एतावत् — इयत्परिमाणम् — परम् ब्रह्म वेद — जानामि। नातः परम् — अस्मात् उत्तरम् — नास्ति।",
      "shankara_bhashya_english": "Shankara: Pippalada humbly says 'I know only this much of Brahman — there is nothing beyond this.' This is the concluding statement of the Prashna Upanishad. The teacher acknowledges the limits of verbal teaching — Brahman in its fullness transcends all description."
    },
